In a large resealable plastic bag, combine the peanut butter, soy sauce, coriander, lemon juice, oil, cumin, chili powder and garlic; add pork. Seal bag and turn to coat; refrigerate several hours or overnight. Meanwhile, combine all sauce ingredients; cover and chill at least 1 hour. Coat grill rack with nonstick cooking before starting the grill. Drain and discard marinade. Thread meat on metal or soaked wooden skewers, leaving a small space between pieces. Grill, covered, over medium for 10-15 minutes or until meat is no longer pink, turning several times. Serve with sauce.